deck: Dilemma can manipulate the Gen-factor of other Gen-actives. She has worked with Tao and Threshold.
description:
Dilemma has the ability to rearrange the Gen-factor of other Gen-actives, causing them to mutate or to gain powers. While working with Tao, she altered Grunge into a giant ape and altered Obidiah Olsen into a teleporter.

Threshold used his mind control to force her to work for him.

Dilemma introduces herself to Sarah Rainmaker as "D". (This plotline is never followed up on.)

issue_credits.name: New Cybertron Part 1: To Walk Among the Chosen

name: Dilemma

deck: Michael Monday was a subject of Project: Genesis along with the members of Gen 13.
description:
Michael Monday is was a powerful telepath who drew strength from other Gen-actives who was part of Project: Genesis along with Gen 13. He was one of the first subject whose Gen-factor became active. He drew strength from the other subjects preventing them from developing, until he was overwhelmed and killed by the power he was absorbed.

He is the son of Helga Kleinman. Helga created a clone of Michael and wiped the clone's memories.

The Michael clone courted Caitlin Fairchild. She considered him to be possibly her only boyfriend. The clone had the same abilities as the original Michael Monday, causing Fairchild to lose her Gen-active powers.

The Michael clone was killed by Ivana Baiul while protecting his mother from Ivana's attack.

issue_credits.name: Fairchild Trilogy (Part 1): Return to Pod Nine

name: Michael Monday

deck: Helga Kleinman was a faculty member at I.O.s Project: Genesis. facility.
description:

Her son Michael was a subject at Project: Genesis. After his death, she cloned him.

deck: Obidiah Olsen is a petty criminal who goes to work for Tao to pay off his gambling debts to the mob.
description:
Obidiah Olsen's genes were rearranged by Dilemma, giving him multiple arms and the ability to teleport. He fought Gen 13 as part of Tao's plot to get Rainmaker to expand the scope of her powers.

Threshold forced Obidiah into working for him.
name: Obidiah Olsen

deck: Gloria Spaulding is the mother of Roxy Spaulding (Freefall).
description:
Although Gloria Spaulding is Roxy Spaulding's biological mother, she raised Roxy to believe that Roxy was her stepdaughter.

Gloria Pellegrino is the daughter of an Air Force colonel. As a seventeen-year-old in New Orleans, she met Alex Fairchild, who fathered Roxy. Gloria ran away to Seattle where she met Aaron Spaulding. Gloria and Aaron married and raised Roxy, telling everyone that she was Aaron's daughter from an earlier marriage.
name: Gloria Spaulding

deck: Terese was a potential love interest for Sarah Rainmaker in New York.
description:
Although Sarah Rainmaker did not initially like living in New York, meeting Terese caused Sarah to reevaluate New York.

Sarah Rainmaker confides to Roxy that she felt a connection to Terese. She decides to return to New York for Terese. Sarah and Terese never meet again.
name: Terese

deck: Bedbug is a villainous adversary to Gen 13.
description:
Bedbug has a long, strong tongue that she can use to strike.

Tao had Bedbug fight Gen 13 as part of his plot to push Rainmaker's powers beyond her control.

Threshold forced Bedbug into working for him.
name: Bedbug

deck: Member of the Moody coven and partner of Piper.
description:
Origin

Very little is known about Noah. A magical being, he at some point met Piper, and joined her to create the Moody coven, based in New York City.

Creation

Noah was created by Ann Nocenti and Trevor McCarthy. He made his first appearance in Klarion #1.

Major Story Arcs

Klarion

Working as the cook for the Moody coven, Noah meets Klarion. Later, he and Piper travel together to the Necropolitan Club, where the fight between Rasp and Klarion has spiralled out of control. Arriving on the scene, they wipe the memories of the bystanders. Returning to his kitchen, he creates a mystic portal which he sends to watch over Klarion and the others. When Klarion and Zell enter Klarion's pocket, Piper and Noah go after them. Arriving in the pocket, he gets into a fight with Beelzebub. Stopped by Piper, he is expelled from the pocket along with the others. When Klarion leaves, Noah helps Piper develop a spell to deal with the monster Gargora, which has been accidentally dragged into reality from Klarion's pocket. He is able to reawaken Teekl, Klarion's familiar, which encourages Klarion to defeat Gargora. Noah works with Klarion and the rest of the coven to defeat Gargora.

Powers and Abilities

Noah is a magical being who is capable of using magic to a variety of effects. He is particularly skilled in the brewing of spells. He is also able to take on the aspects of various animals, for example gaining tough skin or a horn like a rhino.

first_appeared_in_issue.name: There's a New Witch in Town

issue_credits.name: There's a New Witch in Town

name: Oblivion

deck: Leader of the Moody coven.
description:
Origin

Very little is known about Piper's origins. At some point she settled in New York City and created the Moody coven.

Creation

Piper was created by Ann Nocenti and Trevor McCarthy. She made her first appearance in Klarion #1.

Major Story Arcs

Klarion

Piper welcomes the newly-arrived Klarion into the Moody Museum. Later, she and Noah travel together to the Necropolitan Club, where the fight between Rasp and Klarion has spiralled out of control. Arriving on the scene, they wipe the memories of the bystanders and return with the teens to the Museum. There, Piper lectures them on the responsible use of their powers. When Klarion and Zell enter Klarion's pocket, Piper and Noah go after them. She targets Swag, who reveals he has put a wedge between Zell and Klarion, so that Klarion will eventually turn to their side. When Klarion leaves she begins developing a spell to deal with the monster Gargora, which has been accidentally dragged into reality from Klarion's pocket. Her spell awakens Klarion's familiar Teekl, and she encourages Klarion to defeat Gargora. Piper works with Klarion and the rest of the coven to defeat Gargora.

Powers and Abilities

Piper is a magical being with largely unexplored skills. She has displayed the capacity for flight, telekinesis, and energy blasts, among other uses of magic.

deck: Partner of Coal at the Necropolitian Club
description:
Origin

Very little is known about Necrot's origins. At some point he joined up with or was created by Coal, working at the Necropolitan Club and on his efforts to create addictive technology.

Creation

Necrot was created by Ann Nocenti and Trevor McCarthy. He made his first appearance in Klarion #1.

Major Story Arcs

Klarion

Necrot helps Coal manage his technology, and is responsible for monitoring the members of the Moody coven. Though worried by the potential for the technology to get out of their hands, he nonetheless works to further Coal's aims and helps spread the buddybot technology. Following Coal's defeat, Necrot remains with him as he prepares to begin his new schemes.

Powers and Abilities

It is unclear what powers or abilities Necrot possesses, if any. He may be partially robot, as he is described as having been programmed. He may also be a form of zombie or revenant, and he describes himself as "rotting," and requires nanobots for structural integrity.

deck: Demon who Klarion hitches a ride to Earth with
description:
Origin

Beelzebub is a demon of uncertain origin or importance.

Creation

Beelzebub was created by Ann Nocenti and Trevor McCarthy. He made his first appearance in Klarion #1. It is unclear whether he is the real Beelzebub, or merely trading on that name.

Major Story Arcs

Klarion

Driving his car through the multiverse, Beelzebub meets the wandering Klarion. He gives the young witch boy a ride to Earth, describing himself as a barber and offering the boy a "close shave." Leaving him with his card, Beelzebub returns to his barber shop. Some time later he is called by Klarion, asking for the "close shave." He arrives to rescue him from Witchhunter Moody and drives them into Klarion's pocket dimension, where he introduces Klarion to Swag and tries to win him away from the Moody coven. He is confronted by the leaders of the coven, and fights Noah. He escapes the pocket as it begins to collapse, although his car is stolen by Klarion. He meets Klarion at his barber shop and gives him a haircut. After Klarion defeats Coal, he celebrates his downfall.

Powers and Abilities

Beelzebub is a demon of unknown power. His exact powers have never been demonstrated, though he is known to have extensive occult knowledge, and may be capable of independent dimensional travel.
